ntradictory trends in order to gain a sense of the country’s prospects. Reassessing the fascinating and puzzling “Philippines conundrum” from various angles, the analyses contribute sharp and fresh insights into a variety of areas including: the presidency and political parties; constitutional change and federalism; the roles of the military, religion, and the media in politics; the conflict in Mindanao; the communist insurgency; macroeconomic developments, issues, and trends; the investment climate and business opportunities; poverty, unemployment, and income inequality; migration and remittances; and the Philippine development record in comparative perspective. While the analyses offered in this volume do not arrive at a consensus, they provide a deeper perspective and a more balanced appreciation of events in the country and a glimpse of the prospects and challenges that it faces.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Essays.2bisacsh1 aAbinales, Patricio N., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAbueva, Jose V., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBalisacan, Arsenio M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCaballero-Anthony, Mely, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGorospe-Jamon, Grace, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHernandez, Carolina G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJesus, Melinda Quintos de, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKesavapany, K., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMagno, Alexander R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMirandilla, Mary Grace P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/voca